@{b}--(( BUGS ))--@{ub}

Superit was created using AMOS, and as a result there are a few bugs related to AMOS which can directly effect the running of SuperIT.

@{fg shadow}@{bg shine}Date: 20-6-97 By coder Andy Wheeler.@{fg text}@{bg back}

@{b}--MAIN BUGS--@{ub}

1. If you are running Screen Tab, sometimes the newer versions of this program will cause SuperIT to fail to load. The only way around this problem is to disable this program when running SuperIT.@{b}

--MINOR BUGS--@{ub}

1. On some of the level maps a five appears in the top left hand corner of the playing screen. This does not effect the gameplay of SuperIT, its just an annoying bug. This bug will be corrected in later versions of the game.

We would be grateful for any information on bugs that you discover whilest playing the game. Please send your discoveries to the address on the @{"about section" link "About 3AMIGOS" 0} of this guide. With your help SuperIT can only get better!

@{fg shadow}@{bg shine}Date: 21-6-97 By Dave Searle@{fg text}@{bg back}

@{b}--MINOR BUGS--@{ub}

1. While testing the game, we found that it was possible to turn off all the characters so that no one was playing. This isn't very important, we know, because YOU probably won't be that stupid to let no one play! This bug will be corrected in the next version of SuperIT however!
@endnode

